The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 HCL Tech offers 1:1 bonus

 OUR CORRESPONDENT 

 Mumbai, Dec. 14: HCL Technologies today announced a bonus issue in the ratio of 1:1.

 The company would issue an additional share for every one held by the shareholders as on the record date, to be fixed by the board, subject to necessary approvals, HCL Technologies has informed the Bombay Stock Exchange.

 HCL believes in investor friendly policies. For the last 15 quarters, we have been following a high-dividend policy. The bonus issue is a reaffirmation of the policy of rewarding our shareholders and is expected to increase liquidity of the stock and broaden our investor base, Shiv Nadar, chairman and CEO of HCL Technologies, said.

 The company has also declared a final dividend of Rs 4 per share.

 The paid-up share capital of the company is Rs 64.69 crore. It also has reserves and surplus of Rs 2,511.18 crore as on June 30. 

 The company proposes to increase authorised share capital to Rs 150 crore from Rs 125.45 crore.

 The company, listed in January 2000, made a one-for-one stock split in December 2000.

 HCL Technologies recently entered into a strategic alliance with Sage, a Switzerland-based software development company for the financial services industry. The alliance will help develop the Prospero private wealth management application. HCLs banking and financial services practice is six years old. 

 But this alliance is expected to be a product partnership for distribution, marketing and R amp;D capabilities.

 Under the alliance, both companies will work together to develop, distribute and implement Sages flagship product. 




